The paper proposes a method for unsupervised domain adaptation in image classification tasks, which involves learning a classifier in the target domain directly. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as the paper focuses on deep learning-based methods for image classification tasks.
